---
import MarketingLayout from "@/layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";

const jsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "AboutPage",
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Beluga AI",
    "url": "https://beluga-ai.org",
    "description": "An open-source Go framework for production AI agents"
  }
});
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="About Beluga AI — Why Go for AI Agents"
  description="An open-source Go framework for production AI agents. Learn why Go is the right language for AI infrastructure."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-inner">
      <h1 class="about-hero-title">About Beluga AI</h1>
      <p class="about-hero-subtitle">
        An open-source Go framework built for the production side of AI.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="about-prose">
      <h2 class="about-section-title">Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        Go teams building AI products today face a frustrating choice: wrap Python libraries through
        fragile FFI bindings, shell out to Python microservices, or cobble together a patchwork of
        incomplete Go libraries that each cover one small piece of the agent stack. None of these
        paths lead to production-grade systems that Go engineers can reason about, test, and deploy
        with confidence.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beluga AI exists to close that gap. Our vision is a unified, Go-native framework that covers
        the full agent stack &mdash; LLM abstraction, tool execution, RAG pipelines, memory management,
        voice processing, safety guards, and protocol interoperability &mdash; all designed from the
        ground up with Go idioms: interfaces, functional options, explicit error handling, and
        <code>iter.Seq2</code> streaming.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are not competing with Python for ML training or model development. Beluga AI is built for
        the <strong>serving and orchestration layer</strong> &mdash; the part of the stack where Go already
        dominates. The framework is open-source under the MIT license, community-driven, and
        production-focused. Its architecture draws inspiration from Google ADK, OpenAI Agents SDK,
        LangGraph, ByteDance Eino, and LiveKit, unifying their best patterns into a single coherent
        Go framework.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Divider -->
  <div class="about-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <!-- Why Go -->
  <section class="about-section" id="why-go">
    <div class="about-prose">
      <h2 class="about-section-title">Why Go for AI</h2>
      <p class="about-section-lead">
        Go is the language of cloud infrastructure. Here is why it is the right choice for production AI agents.
      </p>

      <!-- Section 1: Performance -->
      <div class="whygo-block">
        <div class="whygo-number">01</div>
        <div class="whygo-content">
          <h3 class="whygo-title">Performance that scales</h3>
          <ul class="whygo-list">
            <li>Compiled to machine code &mdash; no interpreter overhead, no JIT warmup</li>
            <li>Native concurrency via goroutines: thousands of concurrent agent sessions without asyncio complexity or the GIL</li>
            <li>15,000+ RPS with p95 &lt; 30ms for AI orchestration workloads</li>
            <li>75% throughput improvement over Python for production AI infrastructure</li>
            <li>2&ndash;5x smaller container images, reducing cold-start latency and cloud costs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2: Deployment -->
      <div class="whygo-block">
        <div class="whygo-number">02</div>
        <div class="whygo-content">
          <h3 class="whygo-title">Deployment simplicity</h3>
          <ul class="whygo-list">
            <li>Single static binary &mdash; no virtualenvs, no pip, no dependency conflicts</li>
            <li>Cross-compile for any OS and architecture from any development machine</li>
            <li>Container images from ~15MB using scratch or distroless base images</li>
            <li>No runtime dependencies in production &mdash; ship the binary and nothing else</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3: Cloud-native -->
      <div class="whygo-block">
        <div class="whygo-number">03</div>
        <div class="whygo-content">
          <h3 class="whygo-title">Cloud-native alignment</h3>
          <ul class="whygo-list">
            <li>Kubernetes, Docker, Terraform, Prometheus, etcd &mdash; all written in Go</li>
            <li>Native gRPC support with streaming RPCs and interceptor middleware</li>
            <li>First-class OpenTelemetry Go SDK for traces, metrics, and logs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4: Type safety -->
      <div class="whygo-block">
        <div class="whygo-number">04</div>
        <div class="whygo-content">
          <h3 class="whygo-title">Type safety and reliability</h3>
          <ul class="whygo-list">
            <li>Compile-time error checking &mdash; no runtime <code>AttributeError</code> surprises</li>
            <li>Explicit error handling &mdash; every failure path is visible in the code</li>
            <li>Interface-based polymorphism &mdash; swap implementations safely without class hierarchies</li>
            <li>Generics enable <code>iter.Seq2[T, error]</code> for fully typed streaming pipelines</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5: Ecosystem -->
      <div class="whygo-block">
        <div class="whygo-number">05</div>
        <div class="whygo-content">
          <h3 class="whygo-title">The ecosystem is ready</h3>
          <ul class="whygo-list">
            <li>Go's official wiki lists AI as a recognized use case (<a href="https://go.dev/wiki/AI" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">go.dev/wiki/AI</a>)</li>
            <li>Google ADK ships a Go SDK; Firebase Genkit targets Go as a first-class language</li>
            <li>ByteDance's Eino framework is battle-tested in production at TikTok and Doubao scale</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Divider -->
  <div class="about-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <!-- Honest Tradeoffs -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="about-prose">
      <h2 class="about-section-title">What Python still does better</h2>
      <p>
        We believe in honest engineering. Python has the larger ML and deep learning ecosystem &mdash;
        PyTorch, TensorFlow, HuggingFace Transformers, scikit-learn, and thousands of pre-trained
        models are Python-first. The AI research community publishes reference implementations in
        Python, and the sheer volume of tutorials, courses, and Stack Overflow answers makes Python
        the easier on-ramp for data scientists and ML engineers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beluga AI does not try to replace any of that. We are not building a training framework or a
        model inference engine. We are building the <strong>production orchestration layer</strong>
        &mdash; the system that calls LLMs, executes tools, manages agent state, enforces safety
        guardrails, and serves real users at scale. That is where Go excels.
      </p>
      <p class="tradeoff-motto">
        Train in Python, serve in Go.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="about-cta">
    <div class="about-prose" style="text-align: center;">
      <h2 class="cta-title">Ready to build?</h2>
      <p class="cta-desc">Get started with Beluga AI in minutes.</p>
      <div class="about-actions">
        <a href="/docs/getting-started/overview/" class="btn btn-primary">
          Read the Docs
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none">
            <path d="M1 6h10M7 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/lookatitude/beluga-ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-primary">
          Star on GitHub
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none">
            <path d="M3.5 1H11v7.5M11 1L1 11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>

<style>
  /* ── About Hero ── */
  .about-hero {
    padding: 8rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-hero-inner {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-hero-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-primary-gradient);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .about-hero-subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 2.5vw, 1.375rem);
    color: var(--color-text, #999);
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .about-hero-subtitle {
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818) 60%, transparent);
  }

  /* ── About sections ── */
  .about-section {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-section-alt {
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-prose {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-prose p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text, #999);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .about-prose p {
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818) 70%, transparent);
  }

  .about-prose p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-prose strong {
    color: var(--color-light, #f6f6f6);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .about-prose strong {
    color: var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818);
  }

  .about-prose code {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 12%, transparent);
    color: var(--color-primary, #5CA3CA);
    font-family: "SF Mono", "Fira Code", "Fira Mono", monospace;
  }

  .about-prose a {
    color: var(--color-primary, #5CA3CA);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 30%, transparent);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .about-prose a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-primary, #5CA3CA);
  }

  .about-section-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-light, #f6f6f6);
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .about-section-title {
    color: var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818);
  }

  .about-section-lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem !important;
    color: var(--color-text, #999) !important;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem !important;
  }

  /* ── Divider ── */
  .about-divider {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(
      90deg,
      transparent,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-light, #f6f6f6) 12%, transparent) 50%,
      transparent
    );
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .about-divider {
    background: linear-gradient(
      90deg,
      transparent,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818) 12%, transparent) 50%,
      transparent
    );
  }

  /* ── Why Go blocks ── */
  .whygo-block {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 2rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-light, #f6f6f6) 6%, transparent);
  }

  .whygo-block:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .whygo-block {
    border-bottom-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818) 8%, transparent);
  }

  .whygo-number {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
    background: var(--color-primary-gradient);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 3rem;
    padding-top: 0.15rem;
  }

  .whygo-content {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .whygo-title {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-light, #f6f6f6);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .whygo-title {
    color: var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818);
  }

  .whygo-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .whygo-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding: 0.4rem 0 0.4rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text, #999);
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .whygo-list li {
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818) 70%, transparent);
  }

  .whygo-list li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.85rem;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-primary, #5CA3CA);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .whygo-list li code {
    font-size: 0.85em;
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 12%, transparent);
    color: var(--color-primary, #5CA3CA);
    font-family: "SF Mono", "Fira Code", "Fira Mono", monospace;
  }

  .whygo-list li a {
    color: var(--color-primary, #5CA3CA);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 30%, transparent);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .whygo-list li a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-primary, #5CA3CA);
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .whygo-block {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .whygo-number {
      width: auto;
    }
  }

  /* ── Tradeoff motto ── */
  .tradeoff-motto {
    font-size: 1.5rem !important;
    font-weight: 700 !important;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 2rem !important;
    background: var(--color-primary-gradient);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  /* ── CTA ── */
  .about-cta {
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .cta-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    background: var(--color-primary-gradient);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .cta-desc {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text, #999);
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .cta-desc {
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818) 60%, transparent);
  }

  .about-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  /* ── Buttons (reuse from index) ── */
  .btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    transition: transform 0.15s ease, filter 0.15s ease;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
    font-family: inherit;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    transform: scale(1.03);
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--color-primary-gradient);
    color: #fff;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    filter: brightness(1.1);
  }

  .btn-outline-primary {
    position: relative;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--color-light, #f6f6f6);
  }

  .btn-outline-primary::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    padding: 2px;
    background: var(--color-primary-gradient);
    border-radius: inherit;
    mask: linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);
    mask-composite: exclude;
    -webkit-mask-composite: xor;
  }

  .btn-outline-primary:hover {
    background: var(--color-primary-gradient);
    color: #fff;
  }

  :root[data-theme="light"] .btn-outline-primary {
    color: var(--color-lightmode-light, #181818);
  }
</style>
